<entry code="DQC.US.0108.9564" level="error">
 <message filing_url="http://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1653653/000165365326000004/rrr-20251231.htm" severity="error" effectiveDate="2021-09-01" cid="1953895936272">[DQC.US.0108.9564] INCONSISTENT DURATION VALUES: The concept us-gaap:Dividends reports 9,100,000 for a 1-day period (2025-04-30 to 2025-05-01), which exceeds 8,500,000 reported for a longer 365-day period (2024-12-31 to 2025-12-31).

ISSUE: Shorter period values should not exceed longer period values for non-negative monetary concepts.

COMPARISON:
- Shorter period (1 days): 9,100,000 (decimals: -3)
- Longer period (365 days): 8,500,000 (decimals: -3)

FACT DETAILS:
- Period: 2025-05-01 to 2025-05-01
- Dimensions: us-gaap:DistributionsMadeToMemberOrLimitedPartnerByDistributionTypeAxis=rrr:SpecialDividendMember, us-gaap:RelatedPartyTransactionAxis=rrr:FertittaFamilyEntitiesMember
- Unit: USD

ACTION REQUIRED: IF the difference is due to rounding, verify decimal precision is appropriate.

Rule Element ID: 9564
Rule Version: 30.0.0RC1 - rrr-20251231.htm 8</message>
